meta {
  name: Agent Claim Initiate (auth.md POST /agent/identity/claim)
  type: http
  seq: 100
}

post {
  url: {{baseUrl}}/agent/identity/claim
  body: json
  auth: none
}

body:json {
  {
    "claim_token": "{{claimToken}}"
  }
}

vars:pre-request {
  baseUrl: http://localhost:8080
}

docs {
  # POST /agent/identity/claim

  Start (or resume) an auth.md claim ceremony (spec Step 4) for a registration the agent holds a
  `claim_token` for. No auth: the `claim_token` returned by `POST /agent/identity` is the agent's
  credential here — the *user* authorizes later at `.../claim/confirm`.

  This mainly serves the `anonymous` flow, whose registration returned only a `claim_token` and no
  `user_code`. For `service_auth` / first-seen `identity_assertion` a `user_code` was already minted
  at registration, so re-initiating idempotently re-emits the same pending code.

  ## Response (200)

  ```json
  {
    "registration_id": "reg_...",
    "claim_attempt_id": "cla_...",
    "status": "initiated",
    "expires_at": "2026-01-01T00:10:00.000Z",
    "claim_attempt": {
      "user_code": "AB3D9F",
      "expires_in": 600,
      "verification_uri": "https://.../agent/claim",
      "interval": 5
    }
  }
  ```

  Show the user the `user_code` and direct them to the `verification_uri`, where they confirm.

  ## Errors (OAuth-style `{ "error", "error_description" }` body)

  - 400 invalid_request: missing `claim_token`
  - 400 invalid_claim_token: unknown (or revoked) claim token
  - 400 claim_expired: the claim token's TTL has elapsed — re-register
  - 400 claimed_or_in_flight: this registration has already been claimed
}
